# Deploy to: /etc/default/tailscaled on Pi
#
# What this does:
#   Sets tailscaled daemon flags. The default statedir /var/lib/tailscale
#   is on ext4, populated by restore-persistent-state.sh at boot from
#   the FAT32 persistent store.
#
# Why not --statedir on FAT32:
#   Tailscale uses SQLite WAL mode. FAT32 lacks POSIX advisory locks
#   required for WAL shared memory. State corruption or startup failure
#   results. Use restore-script pattern instead.
#
# After first Tailscale auth, copy state back to persistent store:
#   sudo cp -a /var/lib/tailscale/. /boot/firmware/persistent/tailscale/
#
# Verify: systemctl cat tailscaled.service | grep EnvironmentFile

FLAGS=""
PORT="41641"
